  "critical_note": "Equines and cattle together provide all pre-industrial motive power — without draft animals, agriculture and transport are limited to human labor alone",
  "description": "Raising horses (Equus caballus) and donkeys (Equus africanus asinus) for draft power, transport, and pack carrying. Horses provide faster transport and greater pulling power; donkeys are more enduring, tolerate poor forage, and have longer working lifespans (25-30 years vs 15-20 for horses). Both species are essential for pre-industrial motive power.",
